<p>Linear algebra is fundamental to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Image processing (images are matrices of pixels)</li>
<li>Neural networks (weights and activations are matrices)</li>
<li>Data transformations (PCA, feature engineering)</li>
<li>Solving systems of equations efficiently</li>
</ul>
<p>Example: A 28x28 grayscale image is just a 784-dimensional vector!</p>
</span></div>
